snippet.textDisplay:
Ok but why did the tridactlys go to such an evolutionary extreme? Normally traits evolve to the point where more of it is not needed. But two things can push it beyond that point. Tridactyls fell to sexual selection and the Red Queen's Race.

You see to evolution it didn't matter if you live to 900 years or 6 months. Did you leave any little versions of yourself? Did they do so in turn? For a sexually reproducing species that means getting a mate and for makes that often means outcompeting other males. It can be longer talks, bigger antlers to win fights, more elaborate nest building or whatever. Two problems is whatever it is costs and the females want more of it.

The best strategy for females in this situation is to bang the hottest male. This will trend to produce hottie sons who get all the mating opportunities and therefore lots of grandkids. But the daughters are just as significant because dreamboat dad came from a long line of females that favoured hot males. So his daughters will also trend to favour the really gorgeous males which is the right strategy. So the attractive feature in males and the attraction to it in females both grow generation to generation.

Just to keep up males have to increase the amount of whatever females like. That's because the average increases each generation. The males are in an evolutionary arms race - with their own cousins.

Ad this continues less and less males survive to breeding age. Make are born with antlers small enough to run easily in the forest or tails small enough to fly faster than predators. Their greater chance of survival didn't matter next to a lower chance of mating so there are less each year. Those that carry big sexual signals spend more energy going slower. Starvation or predation are more likely.

So the gene pool gets smaller and smaller. Eventually there are too few males even to service the females. Then there's inbreeding. With so few males producing so many babies dad's dad or granddad is more and more likely to be mum's. This can cause fatal birth defects, physical durables or ironically infertility. That's right a strategy aimed at maximising mating can result in a complete inability to do so.

Tridactyls got smarter and smarter, more and more force powerful at the cost of having less and babies per year. The population stopped growing fast enough to make up for the occasional disaster. The less intelligent/force powerful could still breed faster in the wake of a disaster so they should have had the advantage. But the females bred with the more powerful, slower breeding males. The process continued beyond the point of sustainability. Yoda is the pinnacle of a process of becoming more and more attractive to female tridactyls. He could have any female he wanted - if there were any left.

snippet.textDisplay: The REAL problem with Baby Yoda is that it's a useless tool that can only end sadly. The Mandalorian is supposed to be about Boba Fett's backstory, not Baby Yoda. By taking the attention off of Boba, they have turned the show into Quantum Leap. A "hero" goes to a new location every week, meets new co-stars & leaves the place a little better than he left it before. None of the characters matter & Baby Yoda is like Sam Rockwell & Ziggy to Scott Backula. We tune in not to see the main character get home - because if he does - the show ends, but to see what Ziggy will say, or what jokes or glitches will happen with Sam's character. Just like we tune in to see what will Baby Yoda do. The only finality is that we get strung along like fools to only be given a small piece of basically pointless info. Either Baby Yoda is or isn't related to Yoda. A fact that wont really CHANGE the Star Wars universe because now that the baby is considered so important - it will "do" whatever it's meant to do now anyway. Furthermore, if the identity isn't revealed the only other possibility is that it would tie into the movies & become a future trilogy & have something to do with balancing the force. However, why not just do a Yoda origin series with ACTUAL Baby Yoda? So I don't see that happening. This means you'll all watch The Mandalorian for the worst kind of click bait. A show about Boba Fett - that actually isn't about Boba Fett - being sold as a big shocker reveal on Yoda that will never happen, nor turn into anything else other than a tool to sell tickets. If you are okay with mediocre "cop of the week western storytelling" just to find out the answer to a pointless question, fine. That's your choice... but that's the REAL problem with Baby Yoda... not what this "youtube influencer" says.
